    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="In As-Suwayda, dozens of male and female teachers who went to school health building to request referrals and sick leave. Al-Watan found that the number of sick leaves registered during the month of November reached 2,000. In an interview with &quot;Al-Watan&quot; teachers confirmed that the spread of Corona has become a reality and out of concern for themselves, their families and their students in schools, they ask for sick leave, even if they were only suspicious cases. One of the nurses also indicated that the large number of requests for sick leave from the teaching staff is due to their fear of the spread of disease in schools that is associated with the lack of precaution within schools, and that they have students in schools demanding that the teaching process be suspended to cut off a chain of infection, especially as many schools are witnessing significant number of students getting sick without an official decision by their administrations to close classrooms."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 52 65 78 91 104 117 130 143 156 169 182 195 208 221 234 247 260 273 286 299 312 325 338 351 364 377 390 403 416 429 442 455 468 481 494 507 520 533 546 559 572 585 598 611 624 637 650 663 676 689 702 715 728 741 754 767 780 793 806 819 832 845 858 871 884 897 910 923 936 949 962 975 988 1001 1014 1027 1040 1053 1066 1079 1092 1105 1118 1131 1144 1157 1170 1183 1196 1209 1222 1235 1248 1261 1274 1287 1300 1313 1326 1339 1352 1365 1378 1391 1404 1417 1430 1443 1456 1469 1482 1495 1508 1521 1534 1547 1560 1573 1586 1599 1612 1625 1638 1651 1664 1677 1690 1703 1716 1729 1742 1755 1768 1781 1794 1807 1820 1833 1846 1859 1872 1885 1898 1911 1924 1937 1950 1963 1976 1989 2002 2015 2028 2041 2054 2067 2080 2093 2106 2119 2132 2145 2158 2171 2184 2197 2210 2223 2236 2249 2262 2275 2317 2322 2327 2293 2298 2288 2332 2339 2303 2310 2353 2346 2356 2349 2360 2373"/>
